        conseils: "Sarlat market (Saturday morning) is one of France's finest: arrive before 9am. In winter (November-March), the truffle market (Saturday morning, Place de la Liberté) is an event. The historic centre tour takes 2-3 hours on foot. Combine with Beynac (10 km) and La Roque-Gageac (12 km) for a full day. Traditional gabares (flat-bottomed boats) offer Dordogne cruises from La Roque-Gageac. Lascaux IV (25 km) is unmissable: book online.",
